{"id":14334,"date":"2021-02-18T15:39:38","date_gmt":"2021-02-18T20:39:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.yorku.ca\/digitalexperiencehub\/?page_id=14334"},"modified":"2023-03-22T14:06:44","modified_gmt":"2023-03-22T18:06:44","slug":"central-events-calendar-for-super-users","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.yorku.ca\/digitalexperiencehub\/central-events-calendar-for-super-users\/","title":{"rendered":"Central Events Calendar for Super Users"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2>How To Add Event\u200b<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating new events is very straightforward. It is&nbsp;better to prepare the content of the&nbsp;event&nbsp;before attempting to create one. For&nbsp;example, preparing detailed description, venue,&nbsp;time and date,&nbsp;speakers, organizers, labels etc.\u200b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> &nbsp;Hover on M.E. Calendar and click on Add Event.\u200b<\/li><li><strong>Step 2: <\/strong>Add title, fill up events details, select event category and add featured image if available<\/li><li><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Publish<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group grey-bg-block px-5 m-0 has-very-light-gray-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Important fields on event details<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:15px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<ul><li>Date And Time: set the date and time of your event<\/li><li>Event Repeating: for recurring events\u200b if applicable<\/li><li>Hourly Schedule: perfect for speaker series\u200b if applicable<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<ul><li>Organizer:&nbsp;choose event organizers\u200b<\/li><li>Cost: if applicable\u200b<\/li><li>Location\/Venue: physical or virtual?\u200b<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>You are not allowed to add new&nbsp;parent-categories to the events calendar, but you can create sub-categories, organizers.<\/strong><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"border-top pt-2\" id=\"shortcodes\">Approving Events as a Super User<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1: <\/strong>Locate the events in the Events List by navigating to M.E Calendar -&gt; All Events<\/li><li><strong>Step 2: <\/strong>Review the content to ensure its complaint i.e. the submitted event has all the important information such as full event description,&nbsp;time, location and&nbsp;event link if it's a virtual&nbsp;event.<\/li><li><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Publish the event once you have verified that it contains all the required information.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"border-top pt-2\" id=\"shortcodes\">Setting up shortcodes <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This is located in M.E. Calendar &gt; Settings &gt; Shortcodes. Kindly note that to maintain consistency across websites,&nbsp;you should use the full calendar and list view.  This section is divided into two\u200b: <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">Section 1 - Display Options<\/strong><span style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">:<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">This section contains settings to select the look and feel of the calendar<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1: <\/strong>Click Add Shortcode - This will initiate the shortcode wizard to walk you through the process<\/li><li><strong>Step 2: <\/strong>Add shortcode name<\/li><li><strong>Step 3: <\/strong>Select either List View or Full Calendar<\/li><li><strong>Step 4:<\/strong> If List view, select Minimal and if Full Calendar, select Clean style<\/li><li><strong>Step 5: <\/strong>Select \"New Window\"  Single event Display Method<\/li><li><strong>Step 6: <\/strong>Select \"Include expired events\"<\/li><li>Exit the wizard page once you get to the shortcode screen<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">Section 2 - Filter Options<\/strong><span style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">:<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size: revert; color: initial;\">This section contains settings to filter events to show up<\/span>. You can filter by Category, Locations, Organizers, Labels, Tags, etc.<br>To get to this section, you will need to:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1<\/strong>: Exit the shortcode wizard page<\/li><li><strong>Step 2<\/strong>: Refresh the shortcode list page to make your newly created shortcode visible<\/li><li><strong>Step 3<\/strong>: Hover on your shortcode and click edit <\/li><li><strong>Step 4<\/strong>: Scroll to the filter options to add your preferred settings<\/li><li><strong>Step 5<\/strong>: Update.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Shortcode has been generated, the next step is to create an API code which would be used on your website to display the events calendar.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note<\/strong>: <em>For Full Calendar view, use the search form in Block Settings to enable extra search features such as \"text search &amp; search forms\" \u200b<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"border-top pt-2\">Creating shortcode API<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This is located in M.E. Calendar &gt; Settings &gt; Shortcodes<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>On central events calendar website<\/strong>\u200b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> hover on the&nbsp;shortcode&nbsp;you've&nbsp;created and click on create&nbsp;API\u200b<\/li><li><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> choose domain display preference - <ul><li>custom domains if you want to show events on a specific domain - you need to enter your URL<\/li><li>All Domains if you want to show events on any domain the API is applied on.<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> click the&nbsp;generate&nbsp;button<\/li><li><strong>Step 4: <\/strong>Copy the&nbsp;Javascript<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>On your website<\/strong>\u200b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> add \"Custom HTML\" block\u200b<\/li><li><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> paste the&nbsp;Javascript&nbsp;code\u200b<\/li><li><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> update\/Publish the page<\/li><\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-accordion alignnone\"><div class=\"kt-accordion-wrap kt-accordion-wrap kt-accordion-id_fb4b61-f8 kt-accordion-has-3-panes kt-active-pane-0 kt-accordion-block kt-pane-header-alignment-left kt-accodion-icon-style-arrow kt-accodion-icon-side-right\" style=\"max-width:none\"><div class=\"kt-accordion-inner-wrap\" data-allow-multiple-open=\"false\" data-start-open=\"none\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-3 kt-pane_756d8c-0e\" id=\"glendon\"><div class=\"kt-accordion-header-wrap\"><button class=\"kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show\"><span class=\"kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap\"><span class=\"kt-blocks-accordion-title\">French Translation Workaround<\/span><\/span><span class=\"kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger\"><\/span><\/button><\/div><div class=\"kt-accordion-panel\"><div class=\"kt-accordion-panel-inner\">\n<p><strong>Step 1: <\/strong>Create a category specific to Glendon for French events, i.e. \"Glendon French\" as opposed to just \"French\" (so others don't use it)  <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 2: <\/strong>Create\/submit the event twice i.e. one for the English version and the other for French but ensure to select the French category you created in step 1 while creating the French event<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 3: <\/strong>When creating a shortcode, you need to create one to filter only Glendon events which will be posted on English pages and then another shortcode to filter Glendon AND French events which will be posted to your French pages. Details on filtering can be found in Section 2 above.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>How To Add Event\u200b Creating new events is very straightforward. It is&nbsp;better to prepare the content of the&nbsp;event&nbsp;before attempting to create one. For&nbsp;example, preparing detailed description, venue,&nbsp;time and date,&nbsp;speakers, organizers, labels etc.\u200b Step 1: &nbsp;Hover on M.E. Calendar and click on Add Event.\u200b Step 2: Add title, fill up events details, select event category and [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":7,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"kt_blocks_editor_width":"","ngg_post_thumbnail":0},"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v16.7 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Central Events Calendar for Super Users - Digital Experience Hub<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.yorku.ca\/digitalexperiencehub\/central-events-calendar-for-super-users\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Cent